76
00:09:21,625 --> 00:09:27,916
♪ WE'RE WANDERING THE ROAD
NOT YET KNOWN ♪

77
00:09:28,875 --> 00:09:31,416
♪ WE ARE ON A JOURNEY FOREVER ♪

78
00:09:31,500 --> 00:09:35,125
- SOLTY? THAT FOOD,
IS IT FOR ROY?

79
00:09:35,208 --> 00:09:36,833
- YEAH, IT IS.

80
00:09:36,916 --> 00:09:38,625
- DO YOU REALLY THINK
HE'LL EAT ANYTHING?

81
00:09:39,375 --> 00:09:41,833
- HE WILL. I MADE
HIM A SPECIAL DISH,

82
00:09:41,916 --> 00:09:44,583
THE ONE THAT HE AND
ROSE LIKED SO MUCH.

83
00:09:44,666 --> 00:09:45,958
- I HOPE SO.

84
00:09:46,041 --> 00:09:48,333
- I THINK IT'S EXACTLY
WHAT HE NEEDS.

85
00:09:48,416 --> 00:09:50,375
AT TIMES LIKE THIS,
A LITTLE COMFORT FOOD

86
00:09:50,458 --> 00:09:53,416
CAN GO A LONG WAY,
SO JUST KEEP TRYING, OKAY?

87
00:09:53,500 --> 00:09:54,458
- 'KAY!

88
00:09:58,291 --> 00:10:00,083
- Woman on TV: NEIGHBORHOODS
IN THE VICINITY OF THE EXPLOSION

89
00:10:00,166 --> 00:10:01,000
ARE STILL WITHOUT POWER...

90
00:10:01,083 --> 00:10:02,791
- HOW COULD I?

91
00:10:03,625 --> 00:10:05,458
HOW COULD I LET THIS HAPPEN?

92
00:10:08,041 --> 00:10:09,000
AGAIN.

93
00:10:10,500 --> 00:10:11,666
RITA.

94
00:10:11,750 --> 00:10:14,250
- Woman on TV: ...DRINK
BOTTLED WATER UNTIL...

95
00:10:17,250 --> 00:10:18,875
THIS JUST IN, BREAKING NEWS.

96
00:10:18,958 --> 00:10:21,583
JEREMY KOLBEL, IDENTIFIED
AS A SUSPECT IN THE CASE,

97
00:10:21,666 --> 00:10:23,458
HAS REGAINED CONSCIOUSNESS.

98
00:10:23,541 --> 00:10:26,333
RESCUERS PULLED KOLBEL'S BODY
FROM THE WRECKAGE TWO DAYS AGO.

99
00:10:26,416 --> 00:10:28,625
OFFICIALS AT THE HOSPITAL WHERE
SHE WAS TAKEN HAVE CONFIRMED

100
00:10:28,708 --> 00:10:31,083
THAT KOLBEL IS CURRENTLY
UNDER INTENSIVE CARE.

101
00:10:31,166 --> 00:10:33,541
A REPRESENTATIVE FOR
THE R.U.C. STATED THAT...

102
00:10:33,625 --> 00:10:35,458
- THAT'S THE GIRL.

103
00:10:35,541 --> 00:10:37,291
ACCORDING TO ATTENDING
DOCTORS IN THE E.R...

104
00:10:37,375 --> 00:10:39,583
- SHE'S... SHE'S THE ONE.

105
00:10:40,875 --> 00:10:42,166
SHE DID THIS.

106
00:10:43,375 --> 00:10:44,791
IT'S HER FAULT.

107
00:10:44,875 --> 00:10:47,625
- KOLBEL'S ORIGINAL PROGNOSIS
LEFT ONLY A SLIM CHANCE

108
00:10:47,708 --> 00:10:48,875
FOR SURVIVAL.
SO DOCTORS WERE STUNNED...

109
00:10:53,125 --> 00:10:54,583
- ( door bell ringing )

110
00:10:54,666 --> 00:10:57,500
- HI, ROY. I BROUGHT SOME
DINNER IF YOU'RE HUNGRY.

111
00:10:59,875 --> 00:11:00,833
HELLO?

112
00:11:02,666 --> 00:11:03,750
I'M COMING IN.

113
00:11:03,833 --> 00:11:05,291
- ( doorknob clicking )

114
00:11:07,208 --> 00:11:09,083
- ( TV playing indistinctly )

115
00:11:09,500 --> 00:11:10,583
ROY?

116
00:11:11,708 --> 00:11:12,666
HELLO?

117
00:11:14,791 --> 00:11:17,500
- THAT'S STRANGE. DO YOU THINK
HE WENT OUT SOMEWHERE?

118
00:11:17,583 --> 00:11:19,583
- Woman on TV: HER CO-WORKERS
AT ERL DESCRIBE JEREMY KOLBEL...

119
00:11:19,666 --> 00:11:21,166
- OH NO.

120
00:11:21,250 --> 00:11:22,583
- THOUGH AWAY FROM
THE WORKPLACE THEY SAY SHE

121
00:11:22,666 --> 00:11:24,500
FREQUENTLY KEPT TO HERSELF...

122
00:11:37,666 --> 00:11:39,125
- ( groaning)

123
00:11:41,083 --> 00:11:42,250
WATER.

124
00:11:46,208 --> 00:11:47,666
- IT'S BECAUSE OF YOU

125
00:11:48,708 --> 00:11:50,625
THAT RITA'S DEAD!

126
00:11:52,458 --> 00:11:54,458
- ( alarms beeping )

127
00:11:56,333 --> 00:11:57,625
- MISS, WHAT'S WRONG?

128
00:11:58,375 --> 00:11:59,583
- I'M SO SORRY.

129
00:12:01,083 --> 00:12:03,333
I'M SO SORRY.
PLEASE FORGIVE ME.

130
00:12:12,541 --> 00:12:16,500
- ROY, I... I DON'T KNOW HOW YOU
COULD DO SOMETHING LIKE THAT.

131
00:12:18,250 --> 00:12:19,458
WHY, ROY?

132
00:12:23,416 --> 00:12:25,416
- YOU DON'T KNOW A DAMN THING.

133
00:12:27,250 --> 00:12:28,833
- ROY, PLEASE CALM DOWN.

134
00:12:28,916 --> 00:12:30,541
LOOK, IT'S BEEN
A HARD DAY FOR EVERYONE.

135
00:12:30,625 --> 00:12:31,791
LET'S JUST GO HOME AND TALK.

136
00:12:31,875 --> 00:12:33,083
- WHY DID YOU SAVE ME?

137
00:12:35,208 --> 00:12:37,125
WHY DIDN'T YOU
SAVE RITA INSTEAD?

138
00:12:37,208 --> 00:12:38,958
YOU COULD HAVE!

139
00:12:39,041 --> 00:12:41,583
DON'T EVEN PRETEND YOU
UNDERSTAND HOW I FEEL!

140
00:12:41,666 --> 00:12:43,708
BECAUSE YOU CAN'T.
YOU'LL NEVER UNDERSTAND

141
00:12:43,791 --> 00:12:46,041
HOW IT FEELS TO LOSE A DAUGHTER
TWICE IN ONE LIFETIME.

142
00:12:46,125 --> 00:12:49,791
BECAUSE YOU CAN'T FEEL ANYTHING!
YOU'RE JUST A MACHINE!

143
00:12:50,208 --> 00:12:51,458
- ROY!

144
00:12:51,791 --> 00:12:53,291
STOP!

145
00:12:53,375 --> 00:12:54,833
COME BACK!

146
00:12:54,916 --> 00:12:56,125
- ( sobs )

147
00:12:56,208 --> 00:12:57,333
- SOLTY, WAIT!

148
00:13:09,333 --> 00:13:12,083
- Researcher 1: RESPIRATION AND
BLOOD PRESSURE RATES NORMAL.

149
00:13:12,166 --> 00:13:14,958
- Researcher 2: CONFIRMING
EXPANDED BETA WAVES.

150
00:13:15,041 --> 00:13:16,583
- CONTROL SPEED STABLE,

151
00:13:16,666 --> 00:13:19,416
PREPARING TO MEASURE LINES
TWENTY THROUGH TWENTY SIX.

152
00:13:20,291 --> 00:13:22,000
- WAIT. I'M PICKING UP
A FLUCTUATION.

153
00:13:28,000 --> 00:13:29,958
- ( Axela gasping )

154
00:13:30,041 --> 00:13:31,875
- Researcher 1: RESPIRATION
AND HEART RATES RISING RAPIDLY!

155
00:13:33,916 --> 00:13:35,125
- ( gasping )

156
00:13:35,208 --> 00:13:37,083
- Researcher 2:
STRESS COEFFICIENT RISING.

157
00:13:37,166 --> 00:13:39,208
WE HAVE A POSSIBLE REJECTION.

158
00:13:39,291 --> 00:13:41,333
- Researcher 3: WE JUST LOST
LINES SEVEN THROUGH SIXTEEN!

159
00:13:41,416 --> 00:13:43,791
- PUPILS DILATING.
- DECREASE THE CONTROL SPEED.

160
00:13:43,875 --> 00:13:45,416
I'M SHUTTING DOWN
ALL ACTIVE LINES,

161
00:13:45,500 --> 00:13:46,833
SIXTEEN THROUGH THIRTY TWO.

162
00:13:46,916 --> 00:13:48,208
- CONTINUE WITH THE TEST.

163
00:13:49,000 --> 00:13:50,875
- BUT, SIR, THE RISKS ARE...

164
00:13:50,958 --> 00:13:52,458
- CONTINUE.

165
00:13:52,541 --> 00:13:53,750
- YES, SIR.

166
00:13:58,708 --> 00:14:02,458
- ( gasping )

167
00:14:24,416 --> 00:14:25,375
- ( sobbing )

168
00:14:59,541 --> 00:15:02,333
- Axela: I, UH... I'VE GOT
SOMETHING FOR YOU TO SLEEP IN.

169
00:15:03,125 --> 00:15:04,416
I'LL LEAVE IT OUT HERE.

170
00:15:05,833 --> 00:15:06,916
OKAY?

171
00:15:12,541 --> 00:15:13,875
- ( knocking on door )

172
00:15:15,208 --> 00:15:16,833
- HEY, YOU ALL RIGHT IN THERE?

173
00:15:35,791 --> 00:15:38,458
SO, DID SOMETHING HAPPEN TO YOU?

174
00:15:41,208 --> 00:15:42,333
IT'S OKAY.

175
00:15:43,750 --> 00:15:46,125
I'M A GOOD LISTENER
IF YOU WANT TO TALK ABOUT IT.

176
00:15:46,208 --> 00:15:48,333
IT MIGHT HELP YOU FEEL
A LITTLE BETTER TO GET IT OUT.

177
00:15:52,083 --> 00:15:54,375
- ( crying )

178
00:15:55,125 --> 00:15:56,666
- WHAT? WHAT IS IT?

179
00:15:57,666 --> 00:15:58,916
- HE HATES ME!

180
00:15:59,541 --> 00:16:01,333
HE HATES ME!

181
00:16:01,416 --> 00:16:04,875
HE THINKS IT'S ALL MY FAULT.
I DIDN'T SAVE HER.

182
00:16:05,666 --> 00:16:08,000
( sobbing )

183
00:16:25,208 --> 00:16:28,000
- SO THEN, THIS ROY
THAT YOU MENTIONED BEFORE.

184
00:16:28,833 --> 00:16:29,791
IS HE YOUR...

185
00:16:31,125 --> 00:16:33,000
- YES, HE'S MY FATHER.
- ( gasps )

186
00:16:33,875 --> 00:16:35,500
- ( yawns )

187
00:16:38,291 --> 00:16:39,666
SO YOU'RE AWAKE, HUH?

188
00:16:44,875 --> 00:16:46,250
HOLD UP.

189
00:16:46,333 --> 00:16:47,875
- WELL, I, UM...

190
00:16:47,958 --> 00:16:49,875
- I'M TRYING TO SLEEP HERE!

191
00:16:49,958 --> 00:16:51,291
- DADDY, I LOVE YOU.

192
00:16:52,708 --> 00:16:54,250
I LOVE YOU.

193
00:16:54,333 --> 00:16:55,708
- SHE'LL UNDERSTAND SOMEDAY.

194
00:16:59,708 --> 00:17:00,875
- LET'S GO HOME, OKAY?

195
00:17:06,375 --> 00:17:07,625
- HE DOESN'T...

196
00:17:08,375 --> 00:17:09,625
HE DOESN'T WANT ME.

197
00:17:10,708 --> 00:17:12,125
( sobbing )

198
00:17:22,041 --> 00:17:24,666
- ROY, HOW COULD YOU SAY
SUCH HORRIBLE THINGS TO HER?

199
00:17:26,250 --> 00:17:27,583
SOLTY LOVES YOU.

200
00:17:27,666 --> 00:17:30,458
SHE'S BEEN PREPARING YOU MEALS,
BENDING OVER BACKWARDS.

201
00:17:30,541 --> 00:17:32,750
TRYING TO DO EVERYTHING
SHE CAN TO CHEER YOU UP!

202
00:17:33,666 --> 00:17:35,708
DAMMIT! ANSWER ME!

203
00:17:37,333 --> 00:17:38,375
ROY?

204
00:17:39,708 --> 00:17:42,625
- FINE, MAKE ME THE BAD GUY.

205
00:17:42,708 --> 00:17:45,833
BUT WHAT WOULD YOU HAVE
SAID IF IT'D BEEN KASHA? HUH?

206
00:17:48,125 --> 00:17:49,250
GET THE HELL OUT!

207
00:17:49,875 --> 00:17:51,000
GO!

208
00:18:20,208 --> 00:18:21,333
( gasps )

209
00:18:37,125 --> 00:18:38,750
DAMN IT!

210
00:18:38,833 --> 00:18:40,833
WHAT THE HELL
AM I SUPPOSED TO DO?

211
00:18:47,625 --> 00:18:48,666
- SEE YOU IN THE MORNING.

212
00:19:16,458 --> 00:19:17,958
SORRY, I, UM...

213
00:19:18,041 --> 00:19:19,666
I'VE GOT TO LEAVE
FOR WORK NOW, OKAY?

214
00:19:22,291 --> 00:19:23,750
IF YOU GET HUNGRY,
THERE'S PLENTY OF FOOD

215
00:19:23,833 --> 00:19:26,750
IN THE REFRIGERATOR.

216
00:19:26,833 --> 00:19:36,166
TAKE CARE.

217
00:19:36,250 --> 00:19:38,833
- SILVIA BAN AND CELICA
YAYOI RETURNING TO DUTY.

218
00:19:38,916 --> 00:19:40,833
WE WERE TOLD YOU
WISHED TO SEE US, SIR?

219
00:19:41,541 --> 00:19:43,875
- AH, YES, I DID.

220
00:19:43,958 --> 00:19:46,208
I JUST WANTED TO WELCOME
YOU BACK, PERSONALLY.

221
00:19:46,291 --> 00:19:48,791
- THANK YOU.
THANK YOU VERY MUCH, SIR!

222
00:19:48,875 --> 00:19:50,541
- I'M SURE YOU'VE BEEN
FOLLOWING THE NEWS.

223
00:19:50,625 --> 00:19:51,583
THE CLOCK TOWER INCIDENT

224
00:19:51,666 --> 00:19:53,958
REQUIRES YOUR
IMMEDIATE ATTENTION.

225
00:19:54,041 --> 00:19:55,625
LOOK INTO IT AND
REPORT BACK TO ME.

226
00:19:57,875 --> 00:19:59,000
I'M COUNTING ON YOU.

227
00:19:59,083 --> 00:20:00,666
- YES! YES, SIR!

228
00:20:00,750 --> 00:20:01,791
- NOW IF YOU'LL EXCUSE ME,

229
00:20:01,875 --> 00:20:03,250
I HAVE OTHER MATTERS
TO ATTEND TO.

230
00:20:03,333 --> 00:20:05,166
INTEGRA'S BEEN BRIEFED
ON THE INVESTIGATION,

231
00:20:05,250 --> 00:20:06,833
SO DEFER ANY QUESTIONS TO HER.

232
00:20:08,125 --> 00:20:10,125
OH, AND GIRLS,
I ALMOST FORGOT,

233
00:20:10,208 --> 00:20:12,791
I WAS THINKING OF AUTHORIZING
A WELCOME BACK PARTY FOR YOU,

234
00:20:12,875 --> 00:20:13,958
IF YOU WOULDN'T MIND.

235
00:20:14,041 --> 00:20:15,583
- UH, YES SIR. THANK YOU.

236
00:20:17,791 --> 00:20:20,083
- ( giggling ) YOU'RE BLUSHING.
I THOUGHT YOU WERE GONNA

237
00:20:20,166 --> 00:20:21,791
PASS OUT WHEN HE
TOUCHED YOUR SHOULDER.

238
